This paper discusses a data mining tool, specifically clustering, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the evaluation of clusterability, which is a subfield of data mining (cs.DM). The proposed approach involves the use of statistical tests, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and statistics (cs.ST). Finally, the paper focuses on the analysis of real datasets, which is a common theme in social and information sciences (cs.SI).
